   "source": [
    "# Association testing (GWAS)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%load_ext lab_black\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import admix\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "np.random.seed(1234)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dset = admix.io.read_dataset(\"example_data/CEU-YRI\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "admix.Dataset object with n_snp x n_indiv = 15357 x 10000, n_anc=2\n",
       "\tsnp: 'CHROM', 'POS', 'REF', 'ALT', 'QUAL', 'FILTER', 'INFO'"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 3,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [

      "admix.simulate.quant_pheno: 100%|████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████| 2/2 [00:01<00:00,  1.72it/s]"

    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(1000, 2, 10)\n",
      "(10000, 10)\n",
      "(10000, 10)\n"

    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "af_per_anc = dset.af_per_anc()  # calculate allele frequency by ancestry\n",
    "snp_list = dset.snp.index[np.all((0.01 < af_per_anc) & (af_per_anc < 0.99), axis=1)][\n",
    "    0:1000\n",
    "]\n",
    "dset = dset[snp_list, :]  # filter by allele frequency between 1%-99%.\n",
    "\n",
    "# simulate binary phenotypes\n",
    "sim = admix.simulate.quant_pheno(dset, n_causal=2, hsq=0.01, cor=1.0)\n",
    "beta, pheno_g, pheno = sim[\"beta\"], sim[\"pheno_g\"], sim[\"pheno\"]\n",
    "print(beta.shape)  # (n_snp, n_anc, n_sim)\n",
    "print(pheno_g.shape)  # (n_indiv, n_sim)\n",
    "print(pheno.shape)  # (n_indiv, n_sim)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [

       "\tsnp: 'CHROM', 'POS', 'REF', 'ALT', 'QUAL', 'FILTER', 'INFO'"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dset"
   ]
  },
  {

   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sim_i = 0\n",
    "sim_pheno = pheno[:, sim_i]\n",
    "sim_beta = beta[:, :, sim_i]\n",
    "assoc_df = admix.assoc.marginal(\n",
    "    dset=dset,\n",
    "    pheno=sim_pheno,\n",
    "    method=\"ATT\",\n",
    "    family=\"linear\",\n",
    ")"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## HET test\n",
    "\n",
    "HET tests the null hypothesis for coefficients for a set of variables are identical. In the case of two-way admixed populations. It tests the null of \n",
    "$H_0: \\beta_{s,1} = \\beta_{s,2}$ for each SNP $s$.\n",
    "\n",
    "In the following, although we simulate phenotype with no heterogeneity by ancestry, we still get an inflated p-value distribution. This is because the LD induce partial heterogeneity in the effect sizes.\n",
    "\n",
    "Currently HET test is not implemented with cpp so one can expect slower performance. It is recommended to perform HET test in a small subset of variants after LD clumping.\n",
    "\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "# <out>.clumped will be created\n",
    "plink \\\n",
    "    --bfile <bfile> \\\n",
    "    --clump <out>.assoc \\\n",
    "    --clump-p1 5e-8 \\\n",
    "    --clump-p2 1e-4 \\\n",
    "    --clump-r2 0.1 \\\n",
    "    --clump-kb 10000 \\\n",
    "    --memory 20000 \\\n",
    "    --out <out>\n",
    "\n",
    "# get list of clumped SNPs\n",
    "awk '(NF > 0) && (NR > 1) {print $3 }' <out>.clumped > <out>.clumped.snp_list\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
